# How to setup Animate4K

Animate4K is a AI anime upsampling plugin for video player, its usage is not limited by anime, you can use it on other material although not optimized.

Herer I documented how I installed this thing mainly to serve myself. Then i think this may also benefit you. So here it is.



## 1. Download mpv.net player

https://github.com/stax76/mpv.net/releases/

## 2. Download Anime4K shader files

https://github.com/bloc97/Anime4K/releases

## 3. Set Key Bindings for Anime4K

	Open mpv.net player

	right click -> Settings -> Open Config Folders
	
	Create a new folder named 'shaders' in that config folder
	
	Put everything in Anime4K.zip into the root of the folder 'shaders'
	
	Edit the input.conf by text editor
	
	Insert below code at the end of the document
	(Here I changed the original key binding CTRL+NUM to CTRL+Alt+NUM to avoid collision)
	
	After that you can use CTRL+Alt+1 etc to toggle Anime4K
	
		Optimized shaders for higher-end GPU:
		(Eg. GTX 1080, RTX 2070, RTX 3060, RX 590, Vega 56, 5700XT, 6600XT)
		
		> you copy and paste stuff that is below this layer

